radiographic_examinations.findings: A lobulated cystic mass of longitudinal diameter approximately 2.5 cm, occupying the space between the proximal tibia and the fibular neck, located along the anatomical course of the deep and superficial fibular nerves. The lesion showed low to intermediate signal intensity on T1-weighted images and high signal intensity on T2-weighted images, with a cystic appearance due to peripheral enhancement after gadolinium administration.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: On follow-up after 1 month, the clinical picture remained unchanged.
